The paper is about applying dual decomposition and Lagrangian relaxation to inference problems in natural language processing (NLP), which is a subfield of computer science (cs). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also discusses the application of these techniques to machine learning models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Additionally, the paper deals with optimization and combinatorial algorithms, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

Finally, the paper discusses practical issues in implementing the algorithms, which could make it relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
